We will attempt to factor the quadratic now. 

We are looking for two numbers that multiply to 60 (the constant term) and at the same time add to 67 (the coefficient in front of the x).

11x^2 + 67x + 60 = 11x(x + 6) + 1(11x + 10) = 0.

x = -6 with multiplicity one and 
x = -10/11 with multiplicity one.
